# Snippets: Common Run Commands

## 1) Full Pipeline (Recommended)

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File pinescript-agents/tools/run_gex_pipeline.ps1
```

Runs end-to-end:
- Pull historical GEX
- Build NQ/ES Pine blocks
- Refresh multi-asset strategy GEX sections

---

## 2) Pull Historical GEX Only

```powershell
python pinescript-agents/tools/gexbot_pull_historical.py `
  --api-key $env:GEXBOT_API_KEY `
  --tickers NQ_NDX,ES_SPX `
  --aggregation-period zero `
  --start-date 2026-04-17 `
  --end-date 2026-04-18 `
  --skip-weekends `
  --top-n 20 `
  --timeout 30 `
  --sleep-ms 250 `
  --out-dir pinescript-agents/projects/analysis/gexbot_data/historical
```

---

## 3) Build Pine Blocks From Historical Data

### NQ
```powershell
python pinescript-agents/tools/gexbot_nq_to_pine_block.py `
  --dir pinescript-agents/projects/analysis/gexbot_data/historical `
  --require-symbol NQ_NDX `
  --history-out pinescript-agents/projects/generated/nq-gex-history.inc.pine `
  --forward-out pinescript-agents/projects/generated/nq-gex-forward.inc.pine `
  --future-days 30 `
  --skip-weekends-forward
```

### ES
```powershell
python pinescript-agents/tools/gexbot_nq_to_pine_block.py `
  --dir pinescript-agents/projects/analysis/gexbot_data/historical `
  --require-symbol ES_SPX `
  --history-out pinescript-agents/projects/generated/es-gex-history.inc.pine `
  --forward-out pinescript-agents/projects/generated/es-gex-forward.inc.pine `
  --future-days 30 `
  --skip-weekends-forward
```

---

